article.description: Shanae Baker-Brice scored 25 points and Towson stunned Maryland 67-55 to end the Terrapins' five-game winning streak.
article.headline: Baker-Brice's 25 points help Towson shock Maryland
article.linkText: Terps' 5-game streak ends with loss vs. Towson
article.story:
TOWSON, Md. -- Shanae Baker-Brice scored 25 points and Towson stunned Maryland (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) 67-55 on Thursday night to end the Terrapins' five-game winning streak.

The defeat was particularly galling for Maryland (8-2) because it came against a crosstown rival and occurred only three days after the young Terrapins entered the Top 25 for the first time this season.

Maryland shot 34 percent; went 5-for-20 from 3-point range and 8-for-18 at the foul line; and had 18 turnovers. Kim Rodgers scored 15 for the Terrapins, who are 8-0 at home and 0-2 on the road.

Towson (5-4) never trailed after taking a 24-23 lead late in the first half. Baker-Brice went 8-for-13 from the floor and had seven assists.
